ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Eating Disorder Symptom Impact Scale: Nutrition
Notes: Average the scores of items 14, 15, 16, 18, 21, 22, 23, and 24. Lower scores mean a lower tolerability.

ElementDescription: Eating Disorder Symptom Impact Scale: Dysregulated Behavior
Notes: Average the scores of items 10, 11, 12, 13, 17, 19, and 20. Lower scores mean a higher absorption.

ElementDescription: Eating Disorder Symptom Impact Scale: Guilt
Notes: Average the scores of items 5, 6, 7, 8, and 9. Higher scores mean a lower acceptance of distress and perceived ability to cope.

ElementDescription: Eating Disorder Symptom Impact Scale: Social Impact
Notes: Average the scores of items 1, 2, 3, and 4. Lower scores mean a lower tolerability.

ElementDescription: Eating Disorder Symptom Impact Scale: Total Score
Notes: Average the scores of the edsis_n_score, edsis_db_score, edsis_g_score, and edsis_s_score. Higher scores mean a higher distress tolerance.

ElementDescription: Timepoint
Notes: 1 = Screening; 2 = Baseline; 3 = Mid-way; 4 = One Month; 5 = Three Months; 6 = Final
